🅿️🚗 Smart Parking System

📌 Problem Statement:
Finding parking space in cities is frustrating and time-consuming due to the
absence of real-time slot monitoring. Drivers circle endlessly wasting fuel ⛽ and time ⏰.

🎯 Objective:
Design an intelligent parking management system that uses IR sensors to detect
free slots and displays availability on a real-time dashboard 📊 — making parking
stress-free! 😌🚗

🛠️ Hardware & Software Requirements:
• 🖥️ Arduino Uno or NodeMCU
• 📡 IR Proximity Sensors (1 per parking slot)
• 🖥️ LCD Display or Web Dashboard
• 🔌 Jumper wires, breadboard
• 📶 Wi-Fi module (ESP8266) for connectivity

🔬 How It Works:
1️⃣ IR sensors are placed at each parking slot to detect vehicle presence 🚘
2️⃣ Sensor data is collected by Arduino/NodeMCU 📥
3️⃣ Slot availability is displayed in real-time on LCD or web dashboard 📺🌐
4️⃣ Drivers can instantly see which slots are free ✅ or occupied ❌

🏆 Expected Outcome:
A working smart parking model that detects empty slots and updates their
status in real-time on a digital display or web interface 🌐 — reducing traffic
congestion 🚦, saving time ⏱️, and improving urban mobility! 🏙️✨

💡 Technologies Used: Arduino/NodeMCU | IR Sensors | ESP8266 | LCD/Web Dashboard | IoT

